projects:
[{'title': 'GreenMyVibe', 'date': {'start': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': 'The hippies had it figured out all along. The organic farming (today an attractive business model for the F&B industry), healing the planet (today on every science-believing nation’s top most agenda) , treating animals like fellow humans (today every second Facebook post that you see) and all about how all the “elements of mother earth” are in this together (today on everyone’s mind). So before you stereotype this blog as yet another product of an elitist group, we would prefer this blog being seen as an open source of basic, affordable sustainable choices. 

Brought up in two ends of the world (Colombia and the U.A.E.), we moved our lives to the Netherlands in 2017 in hope of being part of a sustainable revolution. Currently, engineers with a master’s degree in Sustainable Energy Technology from TU Delft, we are united by a common goal: Commitment towards sustainability. Commitment towards being heard, commitment towards making a change, no matter how small.
